OL,3,CHospital urges parents to vaccinate
OL,4,Cafter reports a child died from measles
OL,6,FA statement from the Alder Hey
OL,7,FChildren's NHS Foundation Trust said:
OL,8,F"To respect patient confidentiality,
OL,9,Fwe can't comment on individual cases.
OL,11,F"We are concerned about the increasing
OL,12,Fnumber of children and young people
OL,13,Fwho are contracting measles. Measles
OL,14,Fis a highly contagious viral illness
OL,15,Fwhich can cause children to be
OL,16,Fseriously unwell, requiring hospital
OL,17,Ftreatment, and in rare cases, death."
OL,19,FSince June, 17 children have been
OL,20,Ftreated at Alder Hey for complications
OL,21,Flinked to the virus.
